# Intuition
Only the sign bit matter.

# Approach
- 2 negative sign bit cancel each other using xor.
- Early exit on `0`.
- Drag the sign bit over the whole int and set last bit.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: *`O(n)`*
- Space complexity: *`O(1)`*

# Code
```
class Solution { // Vezzz
  public int arraySign(int[] nums) {
    int z = 0;
    for (int v : nums)
      if (v == 0)
        return 0;
      else
        z ^= v;
    return z >> 31 | 1;
  }
}
